    {
      "id": "bc09f8e51134b44f722c78b0f2becfcacfadaf70",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2013-12-10 19:03:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe problem with RHEL6 and SLES11 SP[2/3] is not the lack of cache_register_net/cache_unregister_net but that it is not exported. Looking at the kernels for the distros it can be safely assume that if they are not exported then we need to use cache_register/cache_unregister instead.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5fb2c8e127cfb1feb7cbb41cd2f8fa62de5ffae4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-12-10 22:26:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\nJames, I'm not sure I understand your objection.  If the cache_{un,}register_net() functions are not exported, then this patch is doing exactly what you want - it is calling cache_{un,}register() instead.  The Lustre code itself is using the new calling convention, as it should, so that it is not filled with #ifdefs.  Instead, the cache_{un,}register_net() wrappers are called on older kernels, and the actual functions are called on newer kernels.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "173d6b7fc5a4abca713222bd1e586ccad9b3f4e8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-12-10 22:30:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (4 inline comments)\n\nA few minor improvements if patch needs to be refreshed for some other reason.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "92ae353b25ec3c7618eea5e9e1712415323be761",
      "author": {
